lines.speaker: Hy.
lines.text: O blessed bond of boord and bed:

lines.speaker: Hy.
lines.text: 'Tis Hymen peoples euerie towne,

lines.speaker: Hy.
lines.text: High wedlock then be honored:

lines.speaker: Hy.
lines.text: Honor, high honor and renowne

lines.speaker: Hy.
lines.text: To Hymen, God of euerie Towne.

lines.speaker: Du. Se.
lines.text: O my deere Neece, welcome thou art to me,

lines.speaker: Du. Se.
lines.text: Euen daughter welcome, in no lesse degree.

lines.speaker: Phe.
lines.text: I wil not eate my word, now thou art mine,

lines.speaker: Phe.
lines.text: Thy faith, my fancie to thee doth combine.

lines.speaker: 2. Bro.
lines.text: Let me haue audience for a word or two:

lines.speaker: 2. Bro.
lines.text: I am the second sonne of old {% italic: Sir Rowland, %}

lines.speaker: 2. Bro.
lines.text: That bring these tidings to this faire assembly.

lines.speaker: 2. Bro.
lines.text: {% italic: Duke Frederick %} hearing how that euerie day

lines.speaker: 2. Bro.
lines.text: Men of great worth resorted to this forest,

lines.speaker: 2. Bro.
lines.text: Addrest a mightie power, which were on foote

lines.speaker: 2. Bro.
lines.text: In his owne conduct, purposely to take

lines.speaker: 2. Bro.
lines.text: His brother heere, and put him to the sword:

lines.speaker: 2. Bro.
lines.text: And to the skirts of this wilde Wood he came;

lines.speaker: 2. Bro.
lines.text: Where, meeting with an old Religious man,

lines.speaker: 2. Bro.
lines.text: After some question with him, was conuerted

lines.speaker: 2. Bro.
lines.text: Both from his enterprize, and from the world:

lines.speaker: 2. Bro.
lines.text: His crowne bequeathing to his banish'd Brother,

lines.speaker: 2. Bro.
lines.text: And all their Lands restor'd to him againe

lines.speaker: 2. Bro.
lines.text: That were with him exil'd. This to be true,

lines.speaker: 2. Bro.
lines.text: I do engage my life.

lines.speaker: Du. Se.
lines.text: Welcome yong man:

lines.speaker: Du. Se.
lines.text: Thou offer'st fairely to thy brothers wedding:

lines.speaker: Du. Se.
lines.text: To one his lands with‑held, and to the other

lines.speaker: Du. Se.
lines.text: A land it selfe at large, a potent Dukedome.

lines.speaker: Du. Se.
lines.text: First, in this Forrest, let vs do those ends

lines.speaker: Du. Se.
lines.text: That heere vvete well begun, and wel begot:

lines.speaker: Du. Se.
lines.text: And after, euery of this happie number

lines.speaker: Du. Se.
lines.text: That haue endur'd shrew'd daies, and nights with vs,

lines.speaker: Du. Se.
lines.text: Shal share the good of our returned fortune,

lines.speaker: Du. Se.
lines.text: According to the measure of their states.

lines.speaker: Du. Se.
lines.text: Meane time, forget this new‑falne dignitie,

lines.speaker: Du. Se.
lines.text: And fall into our Rusticke Reuelrie:

lines.speaker: Du. Se.
lines.text: Play Musicke, and you Brides and Bride‑groomes all,

lines.speaker: Du. Se.
lines.text: With measure heap'd in ioy, to'th Measures fall.

lines.speaker: Iaq.
lines.text: Sir, by your patience: if I heard you rightly,

lines.speaker: Iaq.
lines.text: The Duke hath put on a Religious life,

lines.speaker: Iaq.
lines.text: And throwne into neglect the pompous Court.

lines.speaker: 2. Bro.
lines.text: He hath.

lines.speaker: Iaq.
lines.text: To him will I: out of these conuertites,

lines.speaker: Iaq.
lines.text: There is much matter to be heard, and learn'd:

lines.speaker: Iaq.
lines.text: you to your former Honor, I bequeath

lines.speaker: Iaq.
lines.text: your patience, and your vertue, well deserues it.

lines.speaker: Iaq.
lines.text: you to a loue, that your true faith doth merit:

lines.speaker: Iaq.
lines.text: you to your land, and loue, and great allies:

lines.speaker: Iaq.
lines.text: you to a long, and well‑deserued bed:

lines.speaker: Iaq.
lines.text: And you to wrangling, for thy louing voyage

lines.speaker: Iaq.
lines.text: Is but for two moneths victuall'd: So to your pleasures,

lines.speaker: Iaq.
lines.text: I am for other, then for dancing meazures.

lines.speaker: Du. Se.
lines.text: Stay, {% italic: Iaques %}, stay.

lines.speaker: Iaq.
lines.text: To see no pastime, I: what you would haue,

lines.speaker: Iaq.
lines.text: Ile stay to know, at your abandon'd caue.

lines.speaker: Du. Se.
lines.text: Proceed, proceed: wee'l begin these rights,

lines.speaker: Du. Se.
lines.text: As we do trust, they'l end in true delights.
